        <h2>FRQ Questions</h2>
        <div class="frq">
            <h3>Question 1</h3>
            <p>Describe the fundamental attribution error and provide an example of how it might affect our judgment of others.</p>
            <h3>Answer</h3>
            <p>The fundamental attribution error is the tendency to overemphasize personal characteristics and ignore situational factors when judging others' behavior. For example, if someone cuts us off in traffic, we might think they are a rude and inconsiderate person (dispositional attribution) rather than considering they might be rushing to an emergency (situational attribution).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="frq">
